2.what is d/f b/w image and container
Image:
“A Docker image is a read-only snapshot of your application. It contains the application code, dependencies, runtime, libraries, and configuration.
It is built using a Dockerfile and acts as the template for creating containers.”

Container:
“A Docker container is a running instance of a Docker image. It runs the actual application and can store runtime or temporary data.
Containers are isolated, lightweight, and portable.”
